High resolution logo

What is this?

The Premium Package includes multiple high-resolution logo files for all your business and marketing needs.

You'll receive PNG, PDF, EPS (vector) and SVG (vector) files.

Why do I need this?

These different file formats allow you to use your logo in an optimal manner in many contexts:

  • Online: use PNG files for social media or your website
  • Sharing: to share with others, use your PDF files
  • Printing: use EPS files for clear printing at any size (even a billboard)
  • Editing: use SVG files for editing in design software

 

Vector EPS and SVG files

What is this?

An EPS file is a graphics file saved in the Encapsulated PostScript (EPS) file format. It may contain 2D vector graphics, bitmap images, and text.

A file with the SVG file extension is most likely a Scalable Vector Graphics file. Files in this format use an XML-based text format to describe how the image should appear.

Why do I need this?

You’ll only need to use the vector EPS if a printer requests an EPS file, or if you want to make further alterations to your logo. 

There are several reasons why SVG might be used: 

  • Scalable - It’s what the “S” stands for. Unlike traditional images (like PNG or JPG) SVG easily scales from small to big without loss of quality or fidelity.
  • File Size - SVGs are typically smaller files.
  • Modifiable - SVGs aren’t bitmap images therefore they’re easily modified using JavaScript, CSS, Adobe Illustrator or any Adobe program like Photoshop and InDesign. An SVG file can be scaled to different sizes without losing quality.

Transparent background

Why do I need this?

A logo with a transparent background can be crucial to having professional level designs and ads. It gives you more options of where you can place your logo, and allows for a polished look for the end product. You will receive your logo in the following transparent background variations:

  • Coloured logo on a transparent background
  • Black logo on a transparent background
  • White logo on a transparent background

What is this?

The Premium Package includes multiple transparent logo files for all your business and marketing needs.
You’ll receive PNG, PDF, EPS (vector) and SVG (vector) files.

What is this?

You can contact Designhills award winning Customer Success team 7 days a week via:

  • Phone: +1 (888) 765-2908

  • Chat: click the “Help” bubble on the bottom right corner

Why do I need this?

Customers often want assistance with perfecting their logo design, unzipping files, or knowing when to use a specific file type.

Black / White versions

What is this?

The Premium Package includes multiple transparent logo files for all your business and marketing needs.
You’ll receive PNG, PDF, EPS (vector) and SVG (vector) files.

Where could a black/white color logo be used?

Although we live in the digital age, there are still a high number of ‘offline’ locations where a business may need to resort to a black and white version of its logo:

  • Printed logo on Receipts
  • Frosted vinyl’s on glass windows
  • Newspapers and books
  • Promotional Merchandise
  • Logo Engraving / Embossing

Make changes & re-download *

What is this?

This package lets you make instant changes to your logo for the first 3 days after purchase and immediately re-download the associated files. After that, simply email support@designhill.com.

You can edit the colors, fonts, spacing, wording, symbol, and layout directly on your purchased logo during that time.

Why do I need this?

We have noticed, sometimes after a purchase, customers need to edit their purchased logo to make some changes in terms of colors, fonts, spacing, wording, symbol and/or layout. So we realised its best to give every customer that freedom so that you dont have to worry about this! 

Note: Edit option is only available in Premium Package.

Print ready

What is this?

The Premium Package includes multiple high-resolution printable logo files for all your business and marketing needs. 
You’ll receive PNG, PDF, EPS (vector) and SVG (vector) files.

Why do I need this?

Whenever you get your logo printed on your business cards or banners or any other marketing collateral, you would require hi-resolution PNG, or EPS logo files. 

Font names & colors

What is this?

The Premium Package includes a text file that contains important information about your logo design like the font names & color codes. 

Why do I need this?

You would need this information for all your business and marketing needs where you would want to use similar or same fonts and color combinations. 

Full Ownership

What is this?

You’re free to use your purchased logo for any commercial or non-commercial use, and have full ownership of it. The copyright however, applies to your logo as a whole and not the individual elements.

Why do I need this?

We’re always available to prove that you designed your logo on Designhill if you need evidence in a copyright case, though we do not provide any formal documentation. You can use your purchase dates on your receipt as proof of ownership.
